  "Initiated By" : "NATIONAL FUTURES ASSOCIATION",
  "Allegations" : "NFA CASE NO. 10-BCC-026, SEPTEMBER 8, 2010: HAVING REVIEWED THE INVESTIGATIVE REPORT SUBMITTED BY THE COMPLIANCE DEPARTMENT OF THE NATIONAL FUTURES ASSOCIATION (\"NFA\"), AND HAVING FOUND REASON TO BELIEVE THAT NFA COMPLIANCE RULES (\"NFA REQUIREMENTS\") WERE BEING, HAVE BEEN OR ARE ABOUT TO BE VIOLATED AND THAT THE MATTER SHOULD BE ADJUDICATED, NFA'S BUSINESS CONDUCT COMMITTEE (\"BCC\") ISSUED A COMPLAINT AGAINST WILLIAM STEWART MANN.  THE NFA ALLEGED THAT MANN VIOLATED NFA COMPLIANCE RULE 2-9(A).  THE NFA ALLEGED THAT MANN WAS A PRINCIPAL AND AN ASSOCIATED PERSON (\"AP\") OF AN NFA MEMBER GUARANTEED INTRODUCING BROKER (\"IB\") AND AN NFA ASSOCIATE.  THE NFA CHARGED MANN WITH FAILING TO DILIGENTLY SUPERVISE THE SALES ACTIVITY OF THE APS AT HIS FIRM'S NEW YORK BRANCH OFFICE.",
  "Resolution" : "Decision",
  "SanctionDetails" : [ ],
  "Sanctions" : "SANCTIONS DESCRIBED IN COMMENTS",
  "Broker Comment" : "NFA CASE NO. 10-BCC-026, APRIL 21, 2011: THE BCC ACCEPTED THE SETTLEMENT OFFER OF WILLIAM STEWART MANN. THE NFA FOUND THAT MANN FAILED TO SUPERVISE HIS FIRM'S NEW YORK CITY BRANCH OFFICE, IN VIOLATION OF NFA COMPLIANCE RULE 2-9(A). ON APRIL 21, 2011, PURSUANT TO A SETTLEMENT OFFER SUBMITTED BY MANN, THE NFA ORDERED THAT IF, AT ANY TIME PRIOR TO APRIL 1, 2014, HE APPLIES FOR NFA MEMBERSHIP, ASSOCIATE MEMBERSHIP OR PRINCIPAL STATUS WITH AN NFA MEMBER, THEN THIS CASE MAY SERVE AS THE SOLE BASIS FOR DENYING ANY SUCH APPLICATION MADE BY HIM. PURSUANT TO COMMODITY FUTURES TRADING COMMISSION (\"CFTC\") REGULATION 1.63, THE DECISION AND THE SANCTIONS IMPOSED WITHIN RENDER MANN INELIGIBLE TO SERVE ON A DISCIPLINARY COMMITTEE, ARBITRATION PANEL, OVERSIGHT PANEL OR GOVERNING BOARD OF ANY SELF-REGULATORY ORGANIZATION, AS DEFINED IN CFTC REGULATION 1.63, FOR A PERIOD OF THREE YEARS OR UNTIL ALL OF THE SANCTIONS AND CONDITIONS IMPOSED ON HIM HAVE BEEN FULFILLED."
